<subSubSection id="C35A6505FFBC2337FF61FDF8B703FDB4" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFF368EFFBC2337FF61FDF8B703FDB4" blockId="28.[151,1437,433,629]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B934EA9CFFBC2337FF61FDF8B26DFDF0" bold="true" box="[198,309,537,561]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The dissected genitalia of the only known male of this species was found to be missing its aedeagus. However, in all other respects this species comes close to other 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D0DFFBC2337FC9BFDDDB755FD92" box="[828,1037,572,595]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bampurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B934EA9CFFBC2337FC9BFDDDB0E9FD92" box="[828,945,572,595]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Bampurius</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
External distiguishing features of the genus are the head markings (
<figureCitation id="137B2A0BFFBC2337FE72FDBFB168FDB4" box="[469,560,606,629]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–53" captionStartId="62.[151,269,1614,1638]" captionTargetBox="[250,1406,197,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-58@62.[151,1436,175,1671]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURES 52–53. Deltocephalinae genera. 52, Paramesodes iraniensis sp. nov., o: subgenital plate, style, aedeagus and connective, dorsal view; j: male pygofer, dorsal view; q: male pygofer, lateral view. 53, Bampurius melichari (Distant), o: valve, subgenital plate and style, dorsal view." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 53a</figureCitation>
), long antennae and recurved costal forewing veins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
